## Type Coercion (Automatic Type Detection)

Values are automatically converted:

```typescript
// Before parsing (as CSV strings)
// "30" → 30 (number)
// "true" → true (boolean)
// "" → null (null)
// "hello" → "hello" (string)
```

Example:
```typescript
const csv = `name,active,score,notes
John,true,95,Great
Jane,false,88,`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

// result.rows[0].active is boolean true
// result.rows[0].score is number 95
// result.rows[1].notes is null

console.log(typeof result.rows[0].active);   // 'boolean'
console.log(typeof result.rows[0].score);    // 'number'
```

