## Troubleshooting

### "Column not found" error
Make sure the column name matches exactly (case-sensitive)
```typescript
// Wrong
result.sum('Price');  // Error if column is 'price'

// Correct
result.sum('price');
```

### Quoted fields not parsing correctly
Check your quote character matches the data:
```typescript
// If CSV uses single quotes
const result = parseCSV(csv, { quote: "'" });
```

### Type coercion unexpected
Remember: empty strings become null, "null" strings become null, numeric strings become numbers:
```typescript
// "10" → 10 (number)
// "" → null
// "null" → null
// "N/A" → "N/A" (string)
```

### Malformed rows being skipped
Check the errors array for details:
```typescript
if (result.errors.length > 0) {
  result.errors.forEach(e => console.log(e.message));
}
```

